  "original_title": "Fuel shortage hits Suwa Seriya ambulance service",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel shortage hits Suwa Seriya ambulance service",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Suwa Seriya 1990 emergency medical service announced yesterday that its patient transfers would be delayed due to lack of fuel.",
        "In a special notice, the authorities of the service said the number of patients who are taken to hospital daily has risen to 1,600 from 1,000.",
        "\u201cThough the number of patients we have to take to the hospital daily had risen, we face some challenges due to the prevailing situation in the country. We will not be able to transport a patient to the hospital at the average time of 13 to 20 minutes as there will be delays in approaching a person due to the fuel crisis. Also, it has become a hard task for our staff to get to our office on time given the same reason,\u201d the notice said.",
        "However, it was assured that Suwa Seriya would do its utmost to maintain effective medical service to its customers and will always try to respond to service seekers.(YOHAN PERER)"
      ],
